article.description: — Raequan Battle's 29 points, capped by a steal and breakaway layup, helped Montana State defeat Southern Utah 86-83 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Battle's steal, three-point play spark win for Montana State
article.linkText: Battle's steal, three-point play spark win for Montana State
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah -- — Raequan Battle's 29 points, capped by a steal and breakaway layup, helped Montana State defeat Southern Utah 86-83 on Wednesday night. Battle was 10 of 18 shooting, including 7 for 11 from distance, and went 2 for 3 from the line for the Bobcats (4-5). He was fouled on his breakaway layup with 3.6 seconds to go and made the free throw for the final margin. Darius Brown II scored 17 points and added five rebounds and five assists. Great Osobor shot 4 of 5 from the field and 6 for 6 from the line to finish with 14 points, while adding eight rebounds. The Thunderbirds (4-4) were led in scoring by Tevian Jones, who finished with 20 points. Southern Utah also got 17 points and eight rebounds from Harrison Butler. Jason Spurgin had 11 points and three steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
